{
    "componentChunkName": "component---src-templates-post-js",
    "path": "/now-powered-by-gatsby",
    "result": {"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>After <a href=\"/wordpress-to-jekyll\">three and half years of Jekyll</a>, I've made the move over to <a href=\"https://www.gatsbyjs.org/\">GatsbyJS</a>.</p>\n<!-- more -->\n<h2 id=\"introduction\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#introduction\" aria-label=\"introduction permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Introduction</h2>\n<p>GatsbyJS was introduced to me by <a href=\"https://github.com/kiastorm\">Kia Storm</a>, an up and coming frontend developer who previously worked at Autopilot. What stood out to me was the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Progressive_web_application\">Progressive Web App</a> capabilities which made the site feel <strong>FAST</strong>.</p>\n<p>The entire source code can be found on GitHub at <a href=\"https://github.com/calvinbui/calvin.me\">calvinbui/calvin.me</a></p>\n<h2 id=\"goals\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#goals\" aria-label=\"goals permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Goals</h2>\n<p>There were a few things I wanted to achieve with the change.</p>\n<h3 id=\"dark-mode\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#dark-mode\" aria-label=\"dark mode permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Dark Mode</h3>\n<p>Dark mode is available by clicking the Moon icon in the top right corner.</p>\n<h3 id=\"collaboration\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#collaboration\" aria-label=\"collaboration permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Collaboration</h3>\n<p>To make this site more collaborative, it's easier to suggest changes.</p>\n<p>On the top of every post, there's an <em>Edit</em> link which will go straight to repository to create a new PR. Feel free to add your name and a link to your profile on the edit as well.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 420px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/9a4b67ace67969d03bc7df1c7a187431/b0db9/edit-post.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 34.27230046948357%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Edit post button\"\n        title=\"Edit post button\"\n        src=\"/static/9a4b67ace67969d03bc7df1c7a187431/b0db9/edit-post.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/9a4b67ace67969d03bc7df1c7a187431/53f68/edit-post.png 213w,\n/static/9a4b67ace67969d03bc7df1c7a187431/b0db9/edit-post.png 420w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 420px) 100vw, 420px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h3 id=\"rss-feed\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#rss-feed\" aria-label=\"rss feed permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>RSS Feed</h3>\n<p>An RSS feed is available at <a href=\"/rss.xml\">/rss.xml</a> to subscribe to posts. This was a feature a few readers used on WordPress which has removed when moving to Jekyll. This is done using <a href=\"https://www.gatsbyjs.org/packages/gatsby-plugin-feed/\">gatsby-plugin-feed</a>.</p>\n<h3 id=\"easier-to-start-writing\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#easier-to-start-writing\" aria-label=\"easier to start writing permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Easier to start writing</h3>\n<p>Writing a blog post was always a big pain for me. I removed almost all of these pain points:</p>\n<h4 id=\"finding-a-featured-image-and-formatting-it\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#finding-a-featured-image-and-formatting-it\" aria-label=\"finding a featured image and formatting it permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Finding a featured image and formatting it.</h4>\n<p>After writing each post I would have to find a featured image. This image then had to be edited in Photoshop, exported in two sizes (small and large), renamed and optimised using <a href=\"https://nikkhokkho.sourceforge.io/static.php?page=FileOptimizer\">FileOptimizer</a> or <a href=\"https://imageoptim.com/mac\">ImageOptim</a>.</p>\n<p>Now all I have to do is find an image and rename it to <code class=\"language-text\">thumbnail.svg</code> so that <a href=\"https://www.gatsbyjs.org/packages/gatsby-image/\">gatsby-image</a> and <a href=\"https://www.gatsbyjs.org/packages/gatsby-transformer-sharp\">gatsby-transformer-sharp</a> can take care of the rest.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 797px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/ce03a3e1a9458a83da67be6149b50b76/045f5/image.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 71.36150234741784%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"images are the right size\"\n        title=\"images are the right size\"\n        src=\"/static/ce03a3e1a9458a83da67be6149b50b76/045f5/image.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/ce03a3e1a9458a83da67be6149b50b76/53f68/image.png 213w,\n/static/ce03a3e1a9458a83da67be6149b50b76/df70d/image.png 425w,\n/static/ce03a3e1a9458a83da67be6149b50b76/045f5/image.png 797w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 797px) 100vw, 797px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h4 id=\"folder-and-files\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#folder-and-files\" aria-label=\"folder and files permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Folder and files</h4>\n<p>I used to lump all my posts under <code class=\"language-text\">/posts/&lt;slug></code> and images under <code class=\"language-text\">/image/&lt;slug></code>. Now they live together under <code class=\"language-text\">/posts/&lt;slug></code>. This doesn't seem like much but now I don't have to rename two folders when I change a slug anymore!</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"shell-session\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-shell-session line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-shell-session\"><span class=\"token command\"><span class=\"token shell-symbol important\">$</span> <span class=\"token bash language-bash\">tree posts/2020-01-31-managing-the-perfect-csgo-server</span></span>\n<span class=\"token output\">posts/2020-01-31-managing-the-perfect-csgo-server\n├── crosshair.png\n├── index.md\n├── linuxgsm.png\n├── rankme.png\n├── slack-bot.png\n├── thumbnail.png\n└── weaponskin.jpg\n\n0 directories, 7 files</span></code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\n<h4 id=\"remove-duplication-from-post-frontmatter\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#remove-duplication-from-post-frontmatter\" aria-label=\"remove duplication from post frontmatter permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Remove duplication from post frontmatter</h4>\n<p>Frontmatter is a blog at the start of a post's markdown specifying it's metadata such as <code class=\"language-text\">date</code>, <code class=\"language-text\">categories</code>, <code class=\"language-text\">tags</code> and <code class=\"language-text\">title</code>.</p>\n<p>Previously I had a lot of duplicated items in the frontmatter such as the <code class=\"language-text\">slug</code>, <code class=\"language-text\">date</code>, <code class=\"language-text\">featured-image</code>, <code class=\"language-text\">image_directory</code>. These has been removed so only what I need to edit exists.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 603px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/864b8bf91f3b86564e44af9cb83c7ea5/85b8d/frontmatter.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 95.30516431924883%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"difference between frontmatter\"\n        title=\"difference between frontmatter\"\n        src=\"/static/864b8bf91f3b86564e44af9cb83c7ea5/85b8d/frontmatter.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/864b8bf91f3b86564e44af9cb83c7ea5/53f68/frontmatter.png 213w,\n/static/864b8bf91f3b86564e44af9cb83c7ea5/df70d/frontmatter.png 425w,\n/static/864b8bf91f3b86564e44af9cb83c7ea5/85b8d/frontmatter.png 603w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 603px) 100vw, 603px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h4 id=\"browser-reloading\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#browser-reloading\" aria-label=\"browser reloading permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Browser Reloading</h4>\n<p>Developing in GatsbyJS is easy as the browser automatically refreshes!</p>\n<h2 id=\"deployment\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#deployment\" aria-label=\"deployment permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Deployment</h2>\n<p>Moving from Jekyll, I no longer rely on GitHub Pages to build and serve the site. I'm now using a combination of Gatsby Cloud, Netlify and Cloudflare. All of which are free.</p>\n<h3 id=\"gatsby-cloud\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#gatsby-cloud\" aria-label=\"gatsby cloud permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Gatsby Cloud</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gatsbyjs.com/\">Gatsby Cloud</a> is responsible for building the site. It builds the site whenever a new commit is pushed. The free tier provides 25 free builds and previews per day. A really nice feature is that it runs <a href=\"https://developers.google.com/web/tools/lighthouse/\">Google's Lighthouse</a> tool to audit the site.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 619px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/ee312cfaa029e343e6d408007368eeea/80833/lighthouse.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 34.74178403755868%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Google Lighthouse Report\"\n        title=\"Google Lighthouse Report\"\n        src=\"/static/ee312cfaa029e343e6d408007368eeea/80833/lighthouse.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/ee312cfaa029e343e6d408007368eeea/53f68/lighthouse.png 213w,\n/static/ee312cfaa029e343e6d408007368eeea/df70d/lighthouse.png 425w,\n/static/ee312cfaa029e343e6d408007368eeea/80833/lighthouse.png 619w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 619px) 100vw, 619px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h3 id=\"netlify\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#netlify\" aria-label=\"netlify permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Netlify</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://netlify.com/\">Netlify</a> is a CDN responsible for website hosting. It can also build the site and I could move over to it if I wanted.</p>\n<p>The Netlify version of the site is available at <a href=\"https://calvinme.netlify.app/\">https://calvinme.netlify.app/</a></p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 850px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/e6615ad2e254131a88b970a0a2e10e6f/6f18b/netlify.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 42.25352112676056%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"netlify dashboard\"\n        title=\"netlify dashboard\"\n        src=\"/static/e6615ad2e254131a88b970a0a2e10e6f/d6170/netlify.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/e6615ad2e254131a88b970a0a2e10e6f/53f68/netlify.png 213w,\n/static/e6615ad2e254131a88b970a0a2e10e6f/df70d/netlify.png 425w,\n/static/e6615ad2e254131a88b970a0a2e10e6f/d6170/netlify.png 850w,\n/static/e6615ad2e254131a88b970a0a2e10e6f/6f18b/netlify.png 886w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 850px) 100vw, 850px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h3 id=\"cloudflare\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#cloudflare\" aria-label=\"cloudflare permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Cloudflare</h3>\n<p>Cloudflare is responsible for DNS but also it's caching and automatic optimisations. This will reduce Netlify bandwidth usage, which isn't free like GitHub Pages was.</p>\n<h2 id=\"future\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#future\" aria-label=\"future permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Future</h2>\n<p>There are some things that still need to be done:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Hamburger menu on mobile devices for <a href=\"/categories/\">Categories</a> and <a href=\"/tags/\">Tags</a></li>\n<li>Automatically load <code class=\"language-text\">thumbnail.svg</code> instead of having to specify it in the frontmatter</li>\n<li>A fuzzy filter search</li>\n</ul>","timeToRead":4,"excerpt":"After three and half years of Jekyll, I've made the move over to GatsbyJS. Introduction GatsbyJS was introduced to me by Kia Storm, an up…","fileAbsolutePath":"/home/runner/work/calvin.me/calvin.me/master/posts/2020/2020-05-25-now-powered-by-gatsby/index.md","frontmatter":{"title":"Now Powered by Gatsby","categories":["Blog"],"tags":["gatsby","react","netlify"],"thumbnail":{"childImageSharp":null,"extension":"svg","publicURL":"/static/b35bb12e5b3c28c136e7daccb9c0dea3/thumbnail.svg"}}}},"pageContext":{"filter":"/^.*\\/\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}-now-powered-by-gatsby\\/.*$/"}},
